post_cb({"11126801": {"ParentId": "11126203", "PostTypeId": "2", "CommentCount": "3", "Body": "<p>The reason it doesn't work is simply because the Standard forbids it.  Pay special attention to <code>s</code> in the example:</p>\n<p><img alt=\"enter image description here\" src=\"https://i.stack.imgur.com/ELQxE.png\"/></p>\n<p>As a workaround, you can say:</p>\n<pre><code>auto&amp; var = S1::var;\n</code></pre>\n<p>Making the Standard (and therefore all compilers) more complicated to handle an unusual case that has a convenient workaround just doesn't pass the cost-benefit test.</p>\n", "OwnerUserId": "103167", "LastEditorUserId": "103167", "LastEditDate": "2012-06-20T20:54:51.300", "Id": "11126801", "Score": "0", "CreationDate": "2012-06-20T19:29:42.697", "LastActivityDate": "2012-06-20T20:54:51.300"}, "11126203": {"CommentCount": "8", "CreationDate": "2012-06-20T18:50:04.463", "PostTypeId": "1", "AcceptedAnswerId": "11126801", "LastEditorUserId": "1459996", "LastActivityDate": "2012-06-20T20:54:51.300", "LastEditDate": "2012-06-20T19:23:07.990", "ViewCount": "1161", "FavoriteCount": "1", "Title": "Using declaration for a class member shall be a member declaration (C++2003)", "Id": "11126203", "Score": "4", "Body": "<p>Paragraph 7.3.3. of C++2003 standard states that</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_11126203_11126203_0\">Using declaration for a class member shall be a member declaration.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>This means that the following gives a syntax error:</p>\n<pre><code>struct S1\n{\n    static int var1;\n};\n\nusing S1::var1;\n</code></pre>\n<p>While the following compiles fine:</p>\n<pre><code>namespace N2\n{\n    int var2;\n}\n\nusing N2::var2;\n</code></pre>\n<p>Does anybody know the rationale (if any) behind that?</p>\n<p>Even more, the standard gives explicit example with static data member of the struct and tells that it should cause syntax error. MS C++ gives this error:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_11126203_11126203_1\">cpptest1.cxx(9) : error C2885: 'S1::var1': not a valid using-declaration at non-class scope</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>It is still not clear why this should be banned.</p>\n", "Tags": "<c++>", "OwnerUserId": "1459996", "AnswerCount": "1"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_11126203_11126203_0": {"section_id": 253, "quality": 0.8333333333333334, "length": 5}}, "n3337": {"so_11126203_11126203_0": {"section_id": 244, "quality": 0.8333333333333334, "length": 5}}, "n4659": {"so_11126203_11126203_0": {"section_id": 260, "quality": 0.8333333333333334, "length": 5}}}});